Recommends: ollama
Description: Open-source AI assistant for Linux with voice interaction
 Kai is an intelligent voice-activated assistant that runs locally on Linux.
 It features speech recognition, text-to-speech, and integration with
 local LLM models via Ollama.
 .
 Features:
  - Voice interaction with wake word detection
  - Local LLM integration (Ollama)
  - Plugin system for extensibility
  - Privacy-focused (runs entirely locally)
 .
 Note: Some Python dependencies (ollama, rich, SpeechRecognition, gTTS)
 will be installed via pip during post-installation.
